The approach involves exploring reductions from known #P-hard problems (e.g., permanent computation, #SAT) to optimization over $ C_{p^{n+2}} $, possibly leveraging the algebraic properties of LTFs such as Fourier spectra and noise stability. A novel perspective reframes semivalues not as fixed quantities but as solutions to optimization problems, linking explanation robustness to solution sensitivity.

